fields.description:
Enable a simple policy:
{code}
$ aws elb --region us-east-1 --endpoint-url <endpoint>:8773/ set-load-balancer-policies-of-listener --load-balancer-name elb-1 --load-balancer-port 8080 --policy-name tls1.2

$ aws elb --region us-east-1 --endpoint-url <endpoint>:8773/ describe-load-balancer-policies --load-balancer-name elb-1 --policy-name tls1.2
{
    "PolicyDescriptions": [
        {
            "PolicyAttributeDescriptions": [
                {
                    "AttributeName": "Protocol-TLSv1.2", 
                    "AttributeValue": "true"
                }, 
                {
                    "AttributeName": "DHE-RSA-AES256-SHA256", 
                    "AttributeValue": "true"
                }
            ], 
            "PolicyName": "tls1.2", 
            "PolicyTypeName": "SSLNegotiationPolicyType"
        }
    ]
}
{code}

Configuration is changed on the LB:
{code}
$ cat /var/lib/load-balancer-servo/euca_haproxy.conf
...
bind 0.0.0.0:8080 ssl crt /var/lib/load-balancer-servo/elb-cert/cert.pem no-sslv3 no-tlsv10 no-tlsv11 ciphers DHE-RSA-AES256-SHA256
...
{code}

Connecting to the LB with a cipher not defined in the policy succeeds:
{code}
# openssl s_client -cipher CAMELLIA128-SHA -connect <lb>:8080
CONNECTED(00000003)
...
SSL-Session:
    Protocol  : TLSv1.2
    Cipher    : CAMELLIA128-SHA
...
{code}
